A recent survey in urban Shanghai revealed high obesity rates among adults and children, mirroring developed countries.
Improved living standards contribute to the rise, with sedentary lifestyles and high-fat diets as key factors.
Beijing's overweight population also faces similar issues.
Men, ages 7-12 and 60-70, are most at risk.
In Kuwait, hypnotism proves effective in treating obesity.
Psychological factors like anxiety and fear are linked to overeating.
Worldwide, diabetes cases are set to double by 2025 due to aging populations, poor diets, and sedentary habits.
Kuwait and the UAE also grapple with obesity-related health challenges,
